#Defining a variable in Python
country="india"
print(country)
"""
variable name must be descriptive and must begin with a letter or underscore
variable name cannot start with number
Variable name only contains a-Z, 0-9, and _
variable name is case sensitive
value has to be enclosed in double or single quotes
"""
name="John"
age=23
bodyTemperature=98.4
print(name)
print(age)
print(bodyTemperature)
"""
Integers are considered the 'int' type
FLoating point type (float) are variables with real numbers, fractions and/or decimals
All numbers with decimals are the float type
Complex numbers in python are a+bj. a and b are real. j is the sqrt(-1)
"""
number=5+3j
print(number)
"""
A string is a sequence of characters
In python, a string is a sequence of unicode characters
"""
firstName="John"
lastName="Doe"
print(firstName)
print(lastName)
#Storing multiple line string by using triple quotes in the variable#
quote="""Always code as if the guy who ends up 
maintaing your code will be a pyschopath
who knows where you live
-John Woods"""
print(quote)
"""
Boolean (bool) is a true/false expression
Ex. someone logs into site. they won't be able to order until they're logged in
Say logged in is "True" and logged out is "False"
"False" is the default
"""
isLoggedIn=False
#isLoggedIn is the variable name and False is the Boolean value
#Boolean values can also be expressed why writing objective truths and falsehoods
print(5>10)
print(10>5)
#type() returns the data type of a variable
print(type(name))
print(type(age))
print(type(bodyTemperature))
#input() function allows python to read user input from keyboard
username="John"
print(username)
input("Please enter your name")
#To provide a proper response the value from the user must be stored
#Accept the username then print it
username=input("Please enter your name")
print(username)
print(type(username))
#Futher details the User can provide
username=input("please enter your name")
age=input("please enter your age")
print(username)
print(age)
#input only accepts values as string. Type conversion is neccessary
# different type conversions: int(), float(),complex(),bool()
age=int(input("please enter your age"))
print(age)
print(type(age))
